    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="adjust" graphiccount="1">
        <title>Adjust ABS Sensor</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">On units equipped for ABS, push the ABS sensor completely into the sensor bearing until it
                contacts the tone wheel on the hub (Figure 48).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0201248" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg02/G0201248.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="232px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 48. Push ABS Sensor into Sensor Bearing</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SENSOR</callout1>
                <callout1>2. TONE RING</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Do not affect the position of the sensor or allow excess cable to contact the driveshaft.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to Meritor Maintenance Manuals 28 and 30 for service instructions for ABS braking
                systems. To order these publications, contact ArvinMeritor's Customer Service Center at 800-535-5560.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
